Four inmates were killed during an attempted jailbreak in Ile-Ife, Osun State on Tuesday, The Nation has learnt. It was gathered that the incident occurred at the Correctional Center in the Kosere Area of Ile-Ife. A top security source who confided in our correspondent said the inmates attempted to break out of the facility. The source said: “At about a few minutes past 9 am on Tuesday, some inmates after their devotion exercise approached the main entrance of the Centre in the pretence they were going about their normal duties. “While they were wandering at the entrance, they attacked a warder close to the entrance and advanced to escape from the facility. - Advertisement -   Two Lagos pupils hit by truck still hospitalised, says…     We don’t meddle in Ooni’s marital affairs, say…     Burna Boy gifts $3000 to singer who grabbed his foot   “The alertness of the security operatives manning the facility stopped the jailbreak as they shot four of the inmates dead. “The others fled from the entrance where their colleagues attempted to escape from.” Another security source said: “The Controller of Corrections, Olanrewaju Amoran, has visited the scene and the police were involved.” The spokesman of the Centre, Mr Shola Adeotan, told our correspondent: “I will get back to you on the matter.” Spokesperson of Osun State Police Command, Yemisi Opalola, a Superintendent of Police, confirmed the attempted jailbreak. She said: “There was an attempted jailbreak at the Correctional Center, Ile-Ife but information about it is not yet available.”